Source: rinse
Maintainer: Steve Kemp <steve@steve.org.uk>
Section: admin
Priority: extra
Standards-Version: 3.7.2
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)

Package: rinse
Architecture: all
Depends: wget, alien
Description: RPM installation environment
 rinse is a tool for bootstrapping a basic RPM-based distribution of
 GNU/Linux.
 .
 It is comparibly in purpose to the standard Debian debootstrap utility,
 but works upon RPM-based distributions instead.
 .
 Rinse can setup CentOS 4 + 5, and Fedora Core 6.
